overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by adding database capabilities and an admin dashboard. After
  evaluating the existing codebase, a plan was developed to integrate a
  PostgreSQL database (NeonDB) for storing questionnaire responses, implement a
  simple password-based authentication system, and build an admin dashboard for
  data access and CSV export. Key decisions included using Next.js middleware
  for streamlined authentication and updating demographic fields to align with
  project requirements. The implementation involved modifying existing form
  components, creating new Prisma models, and developing several API routes.
  Comprehensive testing confirmed that all core functionalities, including
  database interactions, authentication, and data export, were working as
  expected, providing a robust solution for managing questionnaire data.
